My mum told me an old tale from my village when I was smol: in a house there lived a widow with her six children and her new man - named Sloter. One night during dinner he went to take the knife from the kitchen, when he joked by saying "Uncle Sloter slaughters easily". There was

nothing sinister about the joke, they all started laughing and continued doing so. After a few minutes, they realized he could not stop laughing, with Sloter repeating "Uncle Sloter slaughters easily" in a maniacal fashion. Then something happened to him, he was befallen madness
Old Indian tale, a quick google searcy of black and white wolf would find it

He ended up killing everyone except the younges child, whose sister managed to somehow hide. According to my mother, some nights screams could be heard from the empty house until it was demolished years after. I was always fascinated by this tale - first, because I knew it to be

True due to my mother really being scared to talk about it and second due to the absurdity of it - I believe the man really did not have the intention to commit the murder, that something demonic happened that night, that smth opened a door to another realm and something entered
The child that was hidden by his sister told the neighbours after it escaped AFAIR

It sounds quite "normie" to say, but you definitely should support small local businesses wherever they pop up. A few weeks ago a new street food place popped up in my city, with all kinds of curious treats: homemade chips with different spices, pizza in cone with trad products

Let's be realistic for a moment, you are most likely not bringing down global capitalism or industrial society any time soon - but you most definitely can make a change by supporting a small local business and telling your friends about it. This is the true libertarian spirit!
